  "doc_id": "50566",
  "text": "Perhaps the most popular and extended theory of non-local elasticity is due to Eringen [CITATION_1] . In Eringen's model a non-local stress tensor, computed as an average of the local stress tensor, is introduced. The equation of motion is then expressed in terms of the non-local stress tensor. If the elastic tensor is constant throughout the domain, this theory can be equivalently expressed by replacing the local strain in the constitutive relation for classical elasticity by a non-local one, obtained by averaging [CITATION_2] .",
